text: Lemez-Tamak () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative center of Lemez-Tamaksky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 483 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 15 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Lemez-Tamak
